From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: pai-nix <pai-nix@localhost>
Date: Sun, 3 May 2026 16:35:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 15/15] Add root package.json for PAI runtime dependencies

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1139

A clean PAI v5.0 install ships without a top-level package.json or
node_modules at ~/.claude/. Anything in the install with bare-module
imports crashes at runtime — including security hooks that fire on
every Read tool call (PatternInspector imports `yaml`) and the
broader skill ecosystem (openai, handlebars, replicate, etc.).

Patch 0003 already shipped a PULSE-specific package.json with the
six Pulse-daemon dependencies (smol-toml, grammy,
@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk, minisearch, jose, yaml). That fixed
Pulse but left the root tree without a manifest, so bare-module
imports outside PULSE/ still resolved unpredictably (or crashed).

Affected non-Pulse imports surveyed across hooks/, PAI/TOOLS/, and
skills/:

  yaml             — hooks/security/inspectors/PatternInspector.ts
                     (PreToolUse:Read, fires on every Read)
  openai           — PAI/TOOLS/Inference.ts, multiple skills
  @google/genai    — skills/Research, others
  handlebars       — skills/Prompting (template rendering)
  replicate        — skills/Art, skills/Sales (image generation)
  clsx             — skills/Webdesign UI helpers
  tailwind-merge   — skills/Webdesign UI helpers

This patch ships a root package.json declaring those deps. The
companion `bun install` step in the Nix wrapper (default.nix) runs
at user-install time (right after the existing PULSE/ install), so
node_modules lands at ~/.claude/node_modules and bun's directory-
walking resolution finds the deps from any importer in the tree.

Per the wider design choice (option B in the pai-nix patch series),
bun install runs at user-install time rather than at nix-build time
because Nix's build sandbox blocks network access and a true
fixed-output derivation would require maintaining a hashed bun.lock
across every dep update — not justified for a release-tracking
package. Same pattern as patch 0003 (Pulse package.json).

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json                              NEW (16 lines)

The companion default.nix wrapper change — a `bun install` invocation
at the install root after `cp -r "$PAI_SHARE" "$HOME/.claude"` — is
shipped together with this patch but lives in default.nix, not in
the upstream tarball, so no patch entry for it.
---
 Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json | 16 ++++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 16 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json

diff --git a/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..0000001
--- /dev/null
+++ b/Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/package.json
@@ -0,0 +1,16 @@
+{
+  "name": "pai-root",
+  "version": "5.0.0",
+  "private": true,
+  "description": "PAI root runtime dependencies (hooks, tools, shared skill deps)",
+  "dependencies": {
+    "yaml": "*",
+    "openai": "*",
+    "@google/genai": "*",
+    "handlebars": "*",
+    "replicate": "*",
+    "clsx": "*",
+    "tailwind-merge": "*"
+  }
+}
+
